<TITLE> Moeen's term extended by one year </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 6 (bdnews24.com) The term of Moeen U Ahmed as army chief has been extended by one year to June 15, 2009, an official said Sunday. Sirajul Islam, secretary to the president, told bdnews24.com: "The tenure of the service of the army chief has been extended on a proposal by the Ministry of Defence." The order will come into effect when the army chief's tenure expires in June. The service of Moeen has been extended in the "public interest" following a directive from the president, the Inter-Service Public Relations Directorate said in a statement. Moeen became the chief of the Army Staff of the Bangladesh Army on June 15, 2005. bd
